Pennsylvania Homeless Shelter Offers To-Go Easter DinnersBethesda Mission in Harrisburg hosts a sit-down dinner for the city’s homeless every Easter.
Connecticut Military Children Receive Easter CandyChildren of the Connecticut National Guard recently received bags of Easter candy, donated by Munson’s Chocolates.
Easter Bunny Surprises Children in Staten IslandThe motto at Lucy’s Costume Characters in Staten Island right now is “If you can’t visit the Easter Bunny, we’ll bring the Easter Bunny to you,” reported Staten Island Advance on April 9.
“I wanted to reach as many kids as possible and have them experience time with the Easter Bunny,” the owner, Christine Diana, stressed.
With the help of employees who wanted to pitch in, the Easter Bunny has already visited hundreds of homes.